00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:59,350
or express their own views?

471
00:19:00,560 --> 00:19:01,470
Yes, Li Yitang?

472
00:19:03,280 --> 00:19:04,310
I think that

473
00:19:04,310 --> 00:19:07,110
the ideal state would be
to be loyal to both the law

474
00:19:07,110 --> 00:19:08,310
and the parties involved.

475
00:19:08,430 --> 00:19:09,430
But considering
the professions of lawyers

476
00:19:09,430 --> 00:19:11,400
and legal professionals,

477
00:19:12,230 --> 00:19:14,190
to put it bluntly,

478
00:19:14,230 --> 00:19:16,040
it's about resolving problems
for others in exchange for money.

479
00:19:16,040 --> 00:19:18,040
Therefore, it should be

480
00:19:18,110 --> 00:19:19,920
the interests of the parties involved
that take precedence above all else

481
00:19:19,950 --> 00:19:21,230
within the framework of the law,

482
00:19:21,310 --> 00:19:23,590
to ensure the maximization
of the parties' interests.

483
00:19:23,640 --> 00:19:25,160
That is the ultimate goal we pursue.

484
00:19:25,310 --> 00:19:28,110
As for whether we should
be loyal to the law and justice,

485
00:19:28,310 --> 00:19:29,920
they don't need to worry about that.

486
00:19:30,070 --> 00:19:31,590
It should be reflected in the roles of

487
00:19:32,040 --> 00:19:33,040
prosecutors,

488
00:19:33,110 --> 00:19:35,640
judges, and lawyers.

489
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:45,710
Everyone,

490
00:19:47,350 --> 00:19:48,640
since your first day

491
00:19:49,310 --> 00:19:51,110
of entering this law school,

492
00:19:51,710 --> 00:19:53,040
you should remember

493
00:19:53,520 --> 00:19:56,800
the mission you carry
as legal professionals.

494
00:19:58,830 --> 00:20:00,950
Since I started teaching,

495
00:20:01,710 --> 00:20:04,430
I haven't had the opportunity
to speak up for the parties involved.

496
00:20:05,470 --> 00:20:08,070
But I do consider it fortunate

497
00:20:08,520 --> 00:20:11,160
for me personally.

498
00:20:12,400 --> 00:20:16,830
Today, I want
all of you to remember that

499
00:20:17,430 --> 00:20:20,430
these two aspects are not contradictory,

500
00:20:20,950 --> 00:20:24,350
but rather
the fundamental professional ethics.

501
00:20:25,040 --> 00:20:26,110
Being loyal to the law

502
00:20:26,310 --> 00:20:28,310
and being loyal to the parties involved.

503
00:20:31,110 --> 00:20:33,920
Perhaps there is a misconception here.

504
00:20:34,230 --> 00:20:38,830
Is defending a person known to be guilty

505
00:20:40,040 --> 00:20:41,430
not being loyal to the law?

506
00:20:42,520 --> 00:20:43,190
The answer is

507
00:20:43,640 --> 00:20:45,110
of course not.

508
00:20:45,710 --> 00:20:51,430
According to their professional duties,

509
00:20:51,920 --> 00:20:54,680
lawyers are not obligated to expose
the crimes of the parties involved.

510
00:20:55,920 --> 00:20:56,710
On the contrary,

511
00:20:57,520 --> 00:21:00,520
their duty is to
defend the parties involved.

512
00:21:00,640 --> 00:21:01,520
In other words,

513
00:21:02,310 --> 00:21:03,680
if a lawyer

514
00:21:04,040 --> 00:21:07,160
reveals the crimes
of the parties involved,

515
00:21:08,040 --> 00:21:09,040
then that is

516
00:21:10,040 --> 00:21:11,590
not being loyal to the law.

517
00:21:12,070 --> 00:21:15,000
Legal justice always prevails.

518
00:21:15,350 --> 00:21:16,350
As legal professionals,

519
00:21:16,950 --> 00:21:19,110
we should pursue

520
00:21:19,830 --> 00:21:20,950
procedural justice,

521
00:21:21,350 --> 00:21:24,710
but more importantly,
we should pursue substantive justice.

522
00:21:26,560 --> 00:21:27,230
Perhaps

523
00:21:28,190 --> 00:21:29,190
one day

524
00:21:30,520 --> 00:21:32,430
when you face the realities of life

525
00:21:33,310 --> 00:21:36,110
and have to compromise
for your livelihood,

526
00:21:37,430 --> 00:21:38,830
I hope that all of you

527
00:21:39,280 --> 00:21:41,230
can strike a balance.

528
00:22:00,230 --> 00:22:00,710
(Dad.)

529
00:22:01,230 --> 00:22:03,230
(Regardless of whether
there is a problem with Huiquan,)

530
00:22:03,430 --> 00:22:05,470
(what have you actually done for them.)

531
00:22:06,230 --> 00:22:07,760
(Yesterday was your birthday.)

532
00:22:08,520 --> 00:22:09,520
(As your daughter,)

533
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:11,800
(I shouldn't have embarrassed you)

534
00:22:11,830 --> 00:22:12,950
(in front of your students.)

535
00:22:14,110 --> 00:22:14,520
(Dad.)

536
00:22:15,350 --> 00:22:16,040
(I'm sorry.)

537
00:22:17,520 --> 00:22:18,520
(This cake)

538
00:22:19,110 --> 00:22:21,660
(can be said as a
belated birthday gift for you.)

539
00:22:22,040 --> 00:22:24,560
(Dad, I believe in your character,)

540
00:22:25,830 --> 00:22:27,310
(Although I still can't accept)

541
00:22:27,350 --> 00:22:29,350
(the things that you do in Huiquan,)

542
00:22:30,190 --> 00:22:33,190
(I know you must have your reasons.)

543
00:22:34,680 --> 00:22:37,400
(If you don't want to
explain yesterday's incident,)

544
00:22:38,070 --> 00:22:39,470
(I won't ask again.)

545
00:22:40,560 --> 00:22:41,760
(I won't mention it)

